lead_paragraph: The move came after results of a constitutional amendment removing seniority as the sole determinant of who is chief were certified and as a federal lawsuit seeking to delay implementation is pending.

headline.print_headline: Wisconsin: Justices Vote to Replace Longtime Leader
headline.main: Wisconsin: Justices Vote to Replace Longtime Leader

snippet: The move came after results of a constitutional amendment removing seniority as the sole determinant of who is chief were certified and as a federal lawsuit seeking to delay implementation is pending.
abstract: Wisconsin State Supreme Court judges move to replace longtime Chief Justice Shirley Abrahamson with Justice Patience Roggensack; action follows constitutional amendment removing seniority as lone determinant of who is chief.
